PAPER SUBMISSION
Authors are invited to submit original and unpublished research works=20=20
on the above or other topics related to knowledge management and=20=20
collaboration. Submitted papers must not have been published or=20=20
simultaneously submitted elsewhere.

Papers should be submitted online in either PDF or Ms Word format at=20=20
http://www.theorsociety.com
(Please indicate that your paper is intended for this Special Issue)=20=20
and must comply with the KMRP Instructions to Authors at:
http://www.palgrave-journals.com/kmrp/author_instructions.html
- especially the requirement that author names should not appear=20=20
anywhere in the manuscript file that is submitted. A separate file=20=20
must be submitted containing authors' names, affiliation addresses,=20=20
fax numbers, phone numbers, and email addresses, and brief biographies=20=20
for use if the paper is published.

Normal KMRP reviewing procedures and standards will apply. All papers=20=20
will be double-blind reviewed by at least two reviewers. Papers will=20=20
be selected for publication based on their originality, relevance,=20=20
technical clarity and presentation.  The KMRP web site is=20=20
http://www.palgrave-journals.com/kmrp

The guest editors-in-chief Nada Matta (nada.matta@utt.fr) and In=E8s=20=20
Saad (ines.saad@u-picardie.fr) will be happy to answer any questions.


